      "front": "Second Great Awakening",
      "back": "The popular religious revivals that swept over the country during the Second Great Awakening added a religious underpinning to the celebration of personal self-improvement, self-reliance, and self-determination. And far higher and purer enjoyment has been found in exercises of devotion.\" The Second Great Awakening spread to all regions of the country and democratized American Christianity, making it a truly mass enterprise. Even more than its predecessor of several decades earlier, the Second Great Awakening stressed the right of private judgment in spiritual matters and the possibility of universal salvation through faith and good works.",
